author: Amber Sutton | asutton@al.com
title: See Auburn freshman New Williams' winning dunk during Pearl Jam basketball pep rally
text:
Comments Auburn Dunk Contest Watch the winning dunk of Auburn University freshmen New Williams, of Santa Monica, Calif., during the Pearl Jam basketball pep rally on Oct. 22, 2015, at Auburn Arena. Auburn fans and students gathered at Auburn Arena on Thursday night to enjoy a night filled with laughs, dancing, dunks and more during the second annual Pearl Jam pep rally for the men's basketball team.
During the free fan event, freshman New Williams, of Santa Monica, Calif., showed off his skills by winning the dunk contest with a through-the-legs slam that had the crowd, and his teammates, on their feet. 
In addition, the crowd was treated to a 3-point contest. While Sophomore TJ Lang represented the team well during the competition, Assistant Coach Todd Golden ultimately took home the victory. 
You can see photos of the event and watch video of Williams dunk above.
